{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:46:14.793Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounding Answers in Citations Best Practices"},{"type":"text","text":" are proven strategies for using Claude's Citations API to ensure AI responses are based on uploaded source documents rather than hallucinated information, including techniques like quote-first prompting, source-first synthesis, and strict grounding instructions."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grounding answers means "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"constraining Claude to use only information from uploaded documents"},{"type":"text","text":" with citations proving each claim comes from source text, rather than relying on training data or general knowledge that can lead to hallucinations."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key concept:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The fix isn't more tokens. It's better prompt shapes. Below are eight patterns I use to keep Claude grounded — complete with copy-paste templates and what to watch for.\""}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without Grounding"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With Grounding"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hallucinated claims"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verified, sourced answers"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Footnotes vanish"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Citations for every claim"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Numbers wobble"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exact values from source"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can't answer \"Source?\""}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Page/char references"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Major benefit:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Claude's built-in citation capabilities outperform most custom implementations, increasing recall accuracy by up to 15%.\""}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Grounding Answers"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Source-First, Summary-Second (Evidence Funnel)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Claude tends to generalize early. For research, force a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"quote → citation → summary"},{"type":"text","text":" order.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task: Summarize AFTER gathering evidence.\n\n1) Collect 5–7 high-quality sources on <topic>.\n2) For each source, extract ≤2 DIRECT quotes with line/page refs.\n3) After quotes are collected, write a 150-word synthesis.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{\n  \"quotes\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"<title>\",\n      \"pub\": \"<publisher>\",\n      \"date\": \"<YYYY-MM-DD>\",\n      \"quote\": \"<verbatim up to 30 words>\",\n      \"url\": \"<if available>\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"synthesis\": \"<150-word summary>\"\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Reduces generalization before sourcing\n- Forces evidence collection first\n- Improves accuracy"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Quote-First Prompting"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"For long document tasks, ask Claude to quote relevant parts of the documents first before carrying out its task. This helps Claude stay grounded.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Before answering, quote the relevant passages from the document:\n1. Extract exact quotes with page numbers\n2. Then synthesize the information\n3. Include citations for every claim\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Quotes:\n- \"The methodology used a randomized controlled trial design\" [p. 45]\n- \"Key findings showed 25% improvement in outcomes\" [pp. 78-82]\n\nAnswer:\nThe study used a randomized controlled trial [p. 45] and found 25% improvement [pp. 78-82]."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RAG Grounding Contract"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Grounding with retrieval means you fetch authoritative context (docs, tickets, code snippets) for each user question and instruct Claude to answer using only that retrieved context.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Four-step workflow:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Chunking & indexing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Split docs into 300–800 token chunks with stable IDs and metadata"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Embedding"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create embeddings for each chunk"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Retrieval"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each query, retrieve top-k chunks with metadata filters"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Prompting & rules"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide strict system instruction: \"Use only Context. If missing, say you don't know.\""}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key principle:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The key is not the model—it's the contract. If you don't enforce 'only use Context,' the model may mix in general knowledge.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"System instruction:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use ONLY the provided Context to answer.\nIf the answer is not in Context, say 'I don't know.'\nDo NOT use training data or general knowledge.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Validation:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Add validators: if the answer includes claims without sources, either re-prompt or return 'insufficient context.'\""}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Contrast Tables with Citations"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Battle-tested prompt templates that keep answers factual, sourced, and production-ready for real research work.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Create a comparison table with citations:\n| Aspect | Document A | Document B | Citation A | Citation B |\n|--------|------------|------------|------------|------------|\n| Method | Trial design | Survey | [p. 45] | [p. 12] |\n| Result | 25% improve | 15% improve | [pp. 78-82] | [p. 34] |"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Organizes comparisons clearly\n- Every cell has citation\n- Prevents hallucination"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claim Verification"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Include claim checks in your prompts to catch hallucinations.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"After generating your answer:\n1. Review each claim\n2. Verify it has a citation\n3. If no citation exists, remove the claim or mark it as 'unverified'\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer:\n- The study used a randomized controlled trial [p. 45] ✓\n- Sample size was 500 participants [p. 46] ✓\n- Results were statistically significant [pp. 78-82] ✓\n- Authors recommend policy changes ✗ (unverified - no citation)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error Bars on Uncertainty"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Add error bars for confidence levels to acknowledge uncertainty.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Indicate confidence levels:\n- High confidence: Direct quote with citation [p. X]\n- Medium confidence: Inference from cited text [pp. X-Y]\n- Low confidence: Not in source (mark as 'unverified')\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Acknowledges uncertainty\n- Prevents false confidence\n- Improves accuracy"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Paper-to-Practice Handoff"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Bridge research findings to practical applications with source-grounded guidance.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Translate findings to practice:\n1. Extract findings with citations\n2. Convert to actionable steps\n3. Maintain source references for each recommendation\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Research Finding: \"25% improvement in outcomes\" [pp. 78-82]\n→ Actionable Step: Implement the methodology described on p. 45\n→ Expected Outcome: 25% improvement [pp. 78-82]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"8. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Are You Certain?\" Query"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Consistently ask, 'Are you certain?' It's remarkable how frequently it ends up correcting itself.\""}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"After generating your answer, ask:\n'Are you certain about this claim? Can you verify it has a citation?'\n\nIf not certain, say:\n'Nah man, I just fabricated that, my mistake.'\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Self-corrects hallucinations\n- Reduces false claims\n- Builds honesty"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grounding Checklist"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Do This"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ Don't Do This"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Quote first, then summarize"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summarize before gathering evidence"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use ONLY provided context"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mix in training data/general knowledge"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Require citations for every claim"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let claims go uncited"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Say \"I don't know\" if not in context"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Guess or hallucinate"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Validate claims have sources"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Accept unverified claims"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use error bars for uncertainty"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Present all claims as certain"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Production Grounding Workflow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Complete RAG grounding setup\ndef ground_claude_with_retrieval(query, knowledge_base):\n    # Step 1: Chunk & index\n    chunks = chunk_documents(knowledge_base, size=500)\n    \n    # Step 2: Embed chunks\n    embeddings = create_embeddings(chunks)\n    \n    # Step 3: Retrieve top-k relevant\n    retrieved = retrieve_top_k(query, embeddings, k=5)\n    \n    # Step 4: Prompt with strict grounding\n    system_instruction = \"\"\"\n    Use ONLY the provided Context.\n    If the answer is not in Context, say 'I don't know.'\n    Cite all claims with page/char references.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    context = \"\\n\\n\".join([chunk.text for chunk in retrieved])\n    \n    response = claude.complete(\n        system=system_instruction,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": query}],\n        context=context\n    )\n    \n    # Step 5: Validate claims have sources\n    if not claims_have_citations(response):\n        return \"insufficient context\"\n    \n    return response"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"With Opus 4.6, grounding is especially effective because the model is strong at synthesizing from provided evidence—so the system becomes reliable when the evidence is reliable.\""}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Customer Results"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Metric"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Improvement"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Source hallucinations"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reduced from 10% → 0%"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Formatting issues"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reduced from 10% → 0%"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"References per response"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Increased by 20%"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
